history.content: "First time TA" means that this is your first time TAing at Berkeley.  I know you're required to do the orientation trainings, and I know some of my classmates in CS375 were TAs as undergrads at other institutions, so I take that to mean that if this is the first time you're TAing at Berkeley, you are a "first time TA" even if you've TAed elsewhere.

children.subject:
If you have significant higher-ed TAing / teaching experience, there's precedents for at least getting out of 375, though this was a few years ago. You could check with the GSI recourse center, gsi.berkeley.edu

I think it's worth asking about. 375 is a really fun class, but if you're not going to learn much from it, then y'know, there's better uses of time.

history.content: If we have TAed many times before at another university, are we still considered "first time TA's"? Consequently, do we need to complete all the "first time TA" steps?
history.subject: Definition of "first time TA"
